President Cyril Ramaphosa announces his cabinet - that's after days of speculation of when this will actually happen and after the swearing-in of David Mabuza as an MP yesterday. PRETORIA - President Cyril Ramaphosa will announce his cabinet after days of speculation and the swearing-in of David Mabuza as an MP on Tuesday. READ: Why Ramaphosa had to delay appointing South Africa's next cabinet Many are expecting the president to use his Cabinet announcement to change how his executive and ministries are structured and to reduce it quite significantly. The size of South Africa's Cabinet has ballooned over the years, from 50 members under former president Thabo Mbeki, to 72 members under Jacob Zuma.